<BLIST><TITLE>Macros</TITLE>
  <ITEM>To display the menu to record macros<BR/>
    <CODEMENU>Outils<CODEMENU>Option…</CODEMENU></CODEMENU><BR/>
    In the Options dialog: <CODEMENU>LibreOffice<CODEMENU>Avancé</CODEMENU></CODEMENU>.<BR/>
    Select <CODEMENU>Activer l’enregistreur de macro</CODEMENU>.
  </ITEM>
  <ITEM><BLIST><TITLE>Organisation of macros</TITLE>
    <ITEM><BLIST><TITLE>library container:<BR/>each document is a library container<BR/>the application itself acts as two library containers, <CODEROUTINE>LibreOffice Macros</CODEROUTINE> for macros distributed with LibreOffice and <CODEROUTINE>My Macros</CODEROUTINE> for personal macros.</TITLE>
      <ITEM><BLIST><TITLE>library</TITLE>
        <ITEM><BLIST><TITLE>module</TITLE>
          <ITEM>macro</ITEM>
        </BLIST></ITEM>
      </BLIST></ITEM>
    </BLIST></ITEM>
  </BLIST></ITEM>
  <ITEM>Record the Python source files in <CODEFILENAME>C:\Users\&lt;user&gt;\AppData\Roaming\LibreOffice\4\user\Scripts\python</CODEFILENAME></ITEM>
  <ITEM>Run the macro with <CODEMENU>Outils<CODEMENU>Macros<CODEMENU>Gérer les macros<CODEMENU>Python…</CODEMENU></CODEMENU></CODEMENU></CODEMENU> and select <CODEMENU>Mes macros</CODEMENU></ITEM>
</BLIST><BR/>
